---
/**
 * context-engineering 0002 · Figure 2 — the "find the authentication bug"
 * six-step walk-through stepper.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0002-context-selection-and-retrieval.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes.
 *
 * The connector <line>s in this figure carry NO marker-end, so this figure
 * references none of the page-level shared markers — no <defs> is needed.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 360"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Six-step stepper turning the query find the authentication bug into a packed context window."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Query: &ldquo;find the authentication bug&rdquo;</text
        >

        <!-- step rows -->
        <g font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f">
            <!-- 1 -->
            <circle cx="40" cy="50" r="13" fill="#b5179e"></circle><text
                x="40"
                y="54"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#ffffff">1</text
            >
            <rect x="64" y="36" width="540" height="30" rx="6" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
            ></rect>
            <text x="76" y="50" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
                >Parse entities</text
            >
            <text x="76" y="62"
                >&ldquo;authentication&rdquo; &middot; &ldquo;login&rdquo; &middot;
                &ldquo;token&rdquo; &middot; &ldquo;session&rdquo;</text
            >
            <!-- 2 -->
            <circle cx="40" cy="98" r="13" fill="#b5179e"></circle><text
                x="40"
                y="102"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#ffffff">2</text
            >
            <rect x="64" y="84" width="540" height="30" rx="6" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
            ></rect>
            <text x="76" y="98" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
                >Candidate generation</text
            >
            <text x="76" y="110"
                >lexical: auth/login/session symbols &nbsp;+&nbsp; semantic: the concept</text
            >
            <!-- 3 -->
            <circle cx="40" cy="146" r="13" fill="#1f3a5a"></circle><text
                x="40"
                y="150"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#ffffff">3</text
            >
            <rect x="64" y="132" width="540" height="30" rx="6" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="76" y="146" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
                >Add structural context</text
            >
            <text x="76" y="158"
                >files importing the auth module &middot; its call sites &middot; recent changes</text
            >
            <!-- 4 -->
            <circle cx="40" cy="194" r="13" fill="#1f3a5a"></circle><text
                x="40"
                y="198"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#ffffff">4</text
            >
            <rect x="64" y="180" width="540" height="30" rx="6" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="76" y="194" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
                >Rank candidates</text
            >
            <text x="76" y="206">score by combined signals &middot; best-looking first</text>
            <!-- 5 -->
            <circle cx="40" cy="242" r="13" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
                x="40"
                y="246"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#ffffff">5</text
            >
            <rect x="64" y="228" width="540" height="30" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="76" y="242" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
                >Select top-K within budget</text
            >
            <text x="76" y="254"
                >full body of the prime suspects &middot; signatures/docstrings of the rest</text
            >
            <!-- 6 -->
            <circle cx="40" cy="290" r="13" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
                x="40"
                y="294"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#ffffff">6</text
            >
            <rect x="64" y="276" width="540" height="30" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="76" y="290" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
                >Assemble the window</text
            >
            <text x="76" y="302">prompt + selected context + question, in budget, ordered</text>
        </g>

        <!-- connectors -->
        <line x1="40" y1="63" x2="40" y2="85" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="111" x2="40" y2="133" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="159" x2="40" y2="181" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="207" x2="40" y2="229" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="255" x2="40" y2="277" stroke="#6b675f"></line>

        <text
            x="320"
            y="332"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417"
            >If step 2 or 3 never surfaces the buggy file, no model — however large — can find the
            bug.</text
        >
        <text
            x="320"
            y="348"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#b5179e">Selection quality decides whether the model ever sees the answer.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The whole pipeline can be perfect downstream and still fail if generation misses the file. <b
            >Recall first</b
        > — you cannot rank or pack what you never retrieved.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1c">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
